                ],
                "institute": "1USAMSU"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed at ATLAS",
                "accelerator at Argonne National Laboratory using",
                "helical orbit spectrometer HELIOS."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "CD2 target with thickness of 73 mu-g/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Magnetic spectrometer HELIOS consists of a",
                "superconducting solenoidal magnet with a 2.35-m",
                "long, 0.9-m diameter bore and maximum central field",
                "strength of 1.05 T. The 12B beam was incident along",
                "the magnetic axis of the solenoidal magnet and",
                "passed through the hollow array of position sensitive",
                "silicon detectors arranged along the beam direction."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PS",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Protons corresponding to small center-of-",
                "mass angles are emitted at the backward angles.",
                "In the magnetic field they are detected in the",
                "silicon array with their energy, flight time, and",
                "distance from the target."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SI",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The recoil ions were detected in a Si",
                "telescope consisting of dE and E detectors of",
                "thickness 80 and 500 mu-m, covering laboratory",
                "angles between 0.5deg and 2.8deg."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "EDE",
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Measured using inverse kinematics."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A beam of radioactive 12B (T1/2=20 ms) was produced",
                "using a primary 11B beam, from the ATLAS",
                "accelerator. 11B beam bombarded a cryogenic",
                "deuterium gas cell which yielded a secondary 12B",
                "beam on target with intensity of approximately 10**5",
                "ions/s at 75 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
